the Great East Japan earthquake/tsunami of 11 March 2011. This huge disaster has come to be recorded as part of the “Homeland Paradise Lost” after it saw a majority of the Fukushima region turn to the big japanese junk of nuclear industry — i.e., the Fukushima No.1 Nuclear Plant and Fukushima No. 2 Nuclear Plants which got destroyed by the deadly tsunami in 2011 — this has been recalled to be the first “Homeland Paradise Lost” after it start to trigger the World Horsemen event.

The event marks a total decline from economic and social invulnerability to becoming a total socio-economic basket case for the next half-century to come in the post-Third World War Japanese society akin to that of “Postmodern Japan” in (Daikouken’s) wallpapers, albeit the Japanese society seems to choose its “Homeland Paradise Lost” with relentless vigour. Not being familiar to anything outside of Asia, it would be reasonable to treat this “Homeland Paradise Lost” as only a “token of courtesy to the sun goddess” — presenting itself as society which is not accustomed to “living under foreign rule” for at least a thousand years before 2011 to be led to belief that the islanders do not deserve their windfall in wealth and luxury in the pond called “The “Homeland Paradise Lost”” in which it risks being crushed by a selfish and brutal greed that “offers its purses to be filled” for its benefit through
